  <data name="ProbDescText1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Probability Percentage calculation Logic</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText10" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Revenue Percentage to Distribute : 100 * Revenue to Distribute</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText11" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Now let's calculate the percentiles;</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText12" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>FT1 : 1 / (Revenue Percentage to Distribute * FT1)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText13" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>FT0 : 1 / (Revenue Percentage to Distribute * FT0)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText14" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>FT2 : 1 / (Revenue Percentage to Distribute * FT2)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText15" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Now let's calculate our calculation with the above ratios.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText16" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Profit for the bet group : (1 / 2.0) + (1 / 3.0) + (1 / 2.7) = 0.5 + 0.33 + 0.37 = 1.20</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText17" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Revenue to Distribute : 1 / 1.20 = 0.83</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText18" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Revenue Percentage to Distribute : 0.83 * 100 = %83</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText19" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>We can say that, the bookie is expecting to pay %83 of the total revenues for the match. (bookie is expecting a profit for the bet group : 100 - 83 = %17)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Probability Percentage gives the winning probability of each odd in its own group.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText20" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>FT1: (1/2.0) * 0.83 = 0.415 * 100 = %41.5</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText21" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>FT0: (1/3.0) * 0.83 = 0.276 * 100 = %27.6</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText22" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>FT2: (1/2.7) * 0.83 = 0.307 * 100 = %30.7</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText23" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Finally we have calculated the winning percentage of each odd in its own group.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Assume that the following odds are given by the bookie;</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText4" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Take the betting group as "3 way result" of the match. "3 way result" bets include 3 different betting goals as FT1, FT0 and FT2.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText5" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Assume that Home Win(FT1) : 2.0, Draw (FT0) : 3.0 and Away Win(FT2) : 2.7</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText6" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When profit for the bet group decreases, the profitability of the bookie also decreases.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText7" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Profit for the bet group : (1/HW) + (1/DR) + (1/AW).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText8" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>the total amount to be distributed for 1$ according to the total calculation;</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProbDescText9" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Revenue to Distribute : 1 / Profit for the bet group</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProfitDescText1" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>For the profit percentage, we can also use the term valuebet.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProfitDescText10" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Won Money : 13.75 units</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProfitDescText11" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Our total profit is 13.75 - 22 = -8.25 units. Profit Percentage(ValueBet) : ( (13.75 - 22) / 22 ) * 100 = %-37.5</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProfitDescText2" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Profit percentage gives the percentage of ((total won money - total bet money) / total matches ) * 100</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProfitDescText3" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Let's clarify how we are calculating the profit percentage;</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ProfitDescText4" xml:space="preserve">
